ssing domain and the span of its prosodic correlate. This book will be of interest both to Classicists and to linguists: it aims to solve an old problem in Classical philology, while at the same time working out a configurational syntax for a language with extreme free word order.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aDichtersprache. 4aLatein. 4aLateinische Linguistik. 4aSyntax. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aLatin linguistics.  apoetic language.  asyntax.  aword order.1 aStephens, Laurence D., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut0 cEPUBz97831113861020 cprintz978311138591440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311138606540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111386065423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111386065/original  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles